stories.text:
I'm thinking of making a service that would show young artists in what cities there are a bulk of their fans, so that they could go on tour where it makes the most sense, and so that they could have a joint tour between artists. Spotify does show stats with top cities, but only for artist logged in, not for anyone requested. If I crawl this info from an artist's page, for every my user registered, then I first need everyone registered, which is problematic.

So, dear HN, maybe I'm missing some obvious way so work around that? Or, maybe there are readily available data for me to purchase? Or, should I just beg Spotify to add an api to do that?

Do you need a better version control system? A way to avoid social media during work? Do you need a shiny lib to do X in Ruby? You name it.

Maybe someone already has an app for that or willing to build it.

Please set a price tag you would pay, if you are able to.

Simple brainstorming rules: there are no stupid questions, open mindness, self control.
